SIMPLE: untimely
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Untimely
<hw>Un*time"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not timely; done or happening at
an unnatural, unusual, or improper time; unseasonable; premature;
inopportune; <as>as, <ex>untimely</ex> frosts; <ex>untimely</ex>
remarks; an <ex>untimely</ex> death</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untimely</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Untimely
<hw>Un*time"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Out of the natural or usual
time; inopportunely; prematurely; unseasonably.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Let them
know . . . what's <xex>untimely</xex> done.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untimeous</ent>⟦br⟧
